<item>
            <title>[SOLR-10408] v2 API introspect should return useful message for non-existent command</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-10408</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Instead of failing, v2 API introspect requests that filter for a non-existent command succeed and show &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; for the command spec.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.g., after &lt;tt&gt;bin/solr start -e cloud -noprompt&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;curl &quot;http://localhost:8983/v2/c/gettingstarted/_introspect?method=POST&amp;amp;command=XXXXX&amp;amp;indent=on&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; returns:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;{
  &quot;spec&quot;:[{
      &quot;documentation&quot;:&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/solr/Collections+API&quot;,
      &quot;description&quot;:&quot;Several collection-level operations are supported with this endpoint: modify collection attributes; reload a collection; migrate documents to a different collection; rebalance collection leaders; balance properties across shards; and add or delete a replica property.&quot;,
      &quot;methods&quot;:[&quot;POST&quot;],
      &quot;url&quot;:{&quot;paths&quot;:[&quot;/collections/{collection}&quot;,
          &quot;/c/{collection}&quot;]},
      &quot;commands&quot;:{&quot;XXXXX&quot;:null}}],
  &quot;WARNING&quot;:&quot;This response format is experimental.  It is likely to change in the future.&quot;,
  &quot;availableSubPaths&quot;:{ [...] }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
